description: From Latin supervenīre, present active infinitive of superveniō (“come over or upon, overtake”), from super (“above”) + veniō (“come”).

verbs.description: supervene (third-person singular simple present supervenes, present participle supervening, simple past and past participle supervened)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To follow (something) closely, either as a consequence or in contrast.
To be dependent on an earlier event.
(philosophy) To be dependent on something else for existence, truth, or instantiation.
